race.comment: MR DAMAGE (3) is having his first run since winning by a neck five-and-a-half weeks ago over 1000m at Wauchope. Has transferred to the Troy Clive stable over the break. Shapes well and a bold showing is expected. THREEBROTHERS (4) was a winner over 1000m at Cooktown last time, racing on the pace before getting the upper hand and scoring by 0.6 lengths. In fine form and worth following up. POWER PUFF (9) was a narrow winner two back at this track then in the placings last time at Cooktown. Significant weight drop this time. Is going well this campaign, recording a win and two minor placings from six starts and is capable of going well. COPPABELLA ROAD (10) was a touch disappointing last start when seventh over 1100m at Mackay after he was well back on straightening. Can fill a top-three spot if he brings his A-game.
